open_geotiff[source]

open_geotiff(fn, bands:List[int]=None)

Open geotiff image from path, cast it to float and scale it to 0-1 range, optionally with only bands input bands.

files = os.listdir(data_path)
example = random.sample(files, 1)[0]

tiffile = open_geotiff(data_path/example, bands=[0])
test_eq(type(tiffile), np.ndarray)
test_eq(tiffile.shape[0], 1)
assert tiffile.min() >=0
assert tiffile.max() <= 1

tiffile = open_geotiff(data_path/example, bands=[0,1])
test_eq(type(tiffile), np.ndarray)
test_eq(tiffile.shape[0], 2)
assert tiffile.min() >=0
assert tiffile.max() <= 1

tiffile = open_geotiff(data_path/example)
test_eq(type(tiffile), np.ndarray)
test_eq(tiffile.shape[0], 3)
assert tiffile.min() >=0
assert tiffile.max() <= 1

calc_normalized_spectral_index[source]

calc_normalized_spectral_index(im:ndarray, band_1:int, band_2:int)

Calculate normalized spectral index (band_1 - band_2)/(band_1-band_2). Can be used with NDVI and such

calc_savi[source]

calc_savi(im:ndarray, nir:int, red:int, l:float=0.5)

Calculate Soil Adjusted Vegetation Index ((nir-red)/(nir+red+l)) * (1+l). Default uses Landsat coefficient L

{% endraw %} {% raw %}

def process_reference_data_images(fn:str, plot_radius:float=9)->list:
    tiffile = open_geotiff(fn)
    tiffile = circular_mask(tiffile, plot_radius)
    metrics = calc_metrics(tiffile)
    return metrics
